This document contains the essential Git commands and workflows used during development.

1. ______________INITIALIZE A GIT REPOSITORY______________
If your project is not already a Git repository:
bash
git init

Check the status:
git status

2. ______________ADD FILES TO STAGING______________
Add all new/modified files:
git add .

Add a specific file:
git add path/to/file

3. ______________COMMIT CHANGES______________
Commit staged changes with a message:
git commit -m "Describe what you changed"

View your last few commits:
git log --oneline

4. ______________CONNECT TO A REMOTE GITHUB REPOSITORY______________
Add the remote URL (SSH recommended):
git remote add origin git@github.com:<username>/<repo>.git

If the remote already exists and needs updating:
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:<username>/<repo>.git

Check remotes:
git remote -v

5. ______________PUSH LOCAL BRANCH TO GITHUB______________
If your branch is master:
git push -u origin master

If your branch is main:
git push -u origin main

Future pushes after the first push is done:
git push

6. ______________PULL CHANGES FROM GITHUB______________
Simple pull:
git pull

Pull from a specific branch:
git pull origin master

Pull with rebase (cleaner history):
git pull --rebase origin master

7. ______________COMMON "FIRST PULL" ISSUES______________
If GitHub repo already has commits (e.g., README) and you get:
Updates were rejected because the remote contains work you do not have locally.

Use:
git pull origin master --allow-unrelated-histories

Resolve conflicts if any, then:
git push

8. ______________SSH SETUP______________
Generate SSH key:
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"

Start SSH agent:
ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519

Copy key:
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub

Add the copied key to GitHub → Settings →
Best practice is to give laptop/device name to the key

Test SSH:
ssh -T git@github.com

9. ______________BRANCH BASICS______________
Create a new branch:
git checkout -b feature/new-feature

Switch branches:
git checkout master

List branches:
git branch

Push a new branch:
git push -u origin feature/new-feature

10. ______________VIEWING DIFFERENCES______________
See what changed:
git diff

See staged changes:
git diff --staged

11. ______________UNDOING MISTAKES______________
Unstage files:
git reset HEAD <file>

Undo local modifications (dangerous — use carefully):
git restore <file>

Undo last commit but keep changes staged:
git reset --soft HEAD~1

12. ______________USEFUL TIPS______________
Check which branch you're on:
git branch --show-current

View local + remote branches:
git branch -vv

See remote branches:
git ls-remote --heads origin